49 SECTION 2.
50 Chapter 8 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to employment and
51 training of peace officers, is amended by revising Code Section 35-8-8, relating to
52 requirements for appointment or certification of persons as peace officers and
53 preemployment attendance at basic training course and "employment related information"
54 defined, and by redesignating the current provisions of subsection (c) of said Code section
55 as a new Code section to read as follows:
56 "35-8-8.
57 (a) Any person employed or certified as a peace officer shall:
58 (1) Be at least 18 years of age;
59 (2) Be a citizen of the United States;
60 (3) Have a high school diploma or its recognized equivalent;
61 (4) Not have been convicted by any state or by the federal government of any crime the
62 punishment for which could have been imprisonment in the federal or state prison or
63 institution nor have been convicted of sufficient misdemeanors to establish a pattern of
64 disregard for the law, provided that, for the purposes of this paragraph, violations of
65 traffic laws and other offenses involving the operation of motor vehicles when the
66 applicant has received a pardon shall not be considered;
