67 (5) Be fingerprinted for the purpose of conducting a fingerprint based search at the
68 Georgia Bureau of Investigation and the Federal Bureau of Investigation to determine the
69 existence of any criminal record;
70 (6) Possess good moral character as determined by investigation under procedure
71 established by the council and fully cooperate during the course of such investigation;
72 (7) Be found, after examination by a licensed physician or surgeon, to be free from any
73 physical, emotional, or mental conditions which might adversely affect his or her exercise
74 of the powers or duties of a peace officer; and
75 (8) Successfully complete a job related academy entrance examination provided for and
76 administered by the council in conformity with state and federal law. Such examination
77 shall be administered prior to entrance to the basic course provided for in Code
78 Sections 35-8-9 and 35-8-11. The council may change or modify such examination and
79 shall establish the criteria for determining satisfactory performance on such examination.
80 The provisions of this paragraph establish only the minimum requirements of academy
81 entrance examinations for peace officer candidates in this state; each law enforcement
82 unit is encouraged to provide such additional requirements and any preemployment
83 examination as it deems necessary and appropriate. Any person with a degree from a
84 postsecondary institution accredited by a regional accrediting agency recognized by the
85 United States Department of Education shall be deemed to have met the requirements of
86 this paragraph.
87 (b) Any person authorized to attend the basic training course prior to employment as a
88 peace officer shall meet the requirements of subsection (a) of this Code section.
89 (c) The executive director of the council, or his or her designee, shall promulgate a form
90 which shall be available to any person seeking election to the office of sheriff. Such form
91 shall provide for the attestation and certification by the executive director that the person
92 seeking such form is a certified peace office who is not under revocation or suspension by
93 the council.
